00:18:29,357 --> 00:18:31,148
The client, who else?

268
00:18:31,732 --> 00:18:33,107
How dare you give him my number!

269
00:18:33,148 --> 00:18:34,523
I couldn't refuse.

270
00:18:35,148 --> 00:18:37,565
That's not how it works!
Are you crazy?

271
00:18:38,482 --> 00:18:39,690
He knows all about you.

272
00:18:39,732 --> 00:18:42,732
I didn't tell him
he found out by himself.

273
00:18:42,773 --> 00:18:45,857
He knows that you
tried your hand at acting,

274
00:18:45,898 --> 00:18:47,398
and at times you've
"performed" for me.

275
00:18:48,898 --> 00:18:50,398
Months ago he made me promise

276
00:18:50,440 --> 00:18:52,857
that if you contacted me again
I'd call him.

277
00:18:52,898 --> 00:18:54,732
I couldn't refuse,
he's my best client.

278
00:18:55,167 --> 00:18:56,833
(Hangs)

279
00:18:58,917 --> 00:19:05,667
(Phone)

280
00:19:08,608 --> 00:19:09,171
Yes?

281
00:19:09,171 --> 00:19:10,315
Oh, Magdalena!

282
00:19:11,148 --> 00:19:12,398
Mom, how's dad?

283
00:19:13,190 --> 00:19:14,356
Awful!

284
00:19:15,231 --> 00:19:17,231
We had a terrible night.

285
00:19:17,273 --> 00:19:20,148
He's been vomiting blood
and everything.

286
00:19:20,190 --> 00:19:24,106
it's like he'd burst inside.
I don't know what to do.

287
00:19:24,523 --> 00:19:25,440
I'm coming.

288
00:19:29,042 --> 00:19:34,208
(Phone)

289
00:19:40,368 --> 00:19:41,128
Yes?

290
00:19:41,163 --> 00:19:42,856
Mr. Martel? It's Lena.

291
00:19:45,440 --> 00:19:47,065
I'm sorry to bother you.

292
00:19:47,106 --> 00:19:48,356
You never bother me.

293
00:19:49,940 --> 00:19:52,398
I'm calling because
my father is dying.

294
00:19:52,606 --> 00:19:54,190
He has to be hospitalized,

295
00:19:54,231 --> 00:19:56,065
but i don't know where.

296
00:19:56,398 --> 00:20:00,940
They sent him home yesterday
and we don't know what to do.

297
00:20:01,481 --> 00:20:02,815
Don't worry.

298
00:20:03,440 --> 00:20:06,690
We'll take him to a private clinic.

299
00:20:06,731 --> 00:20:07,773
I'll take care of it.

300
00:20:08,606 --> 00:20:12,273
Don't worry, Dr. Blasco is
the best digestive surgeon in Europe.

301
00:20:12,315 --> 00:20:13,856
Here.

302
00:20:17,356 --> 00:20:18,815
How's the patient?

303
00:20:18,856 --> 00:20:21,981
He arrived in very poor condition.
I think you know that.

304
00:20:22,023 --> 00:20:23,481
Can you save him?

305
00:20:23,523 --> 00:20:25,315
I am Ernesto Martel.

306
00:20:25,356 --> 00:20:27,023
We'll try our very best.

307
00:20:27,065 --> 00:20:30,481
- But right now we can't operate.
- And tomorrow?

308
00:20:30,856 --> 00:20:33,773
Perhaps.
We're feeding him intravenously

309
00:20:33,815 --> 00:20:36,356
and he'll need a transfusion
to survive.

310
00:20:36,398 --> 00:20:38,731
Do the impossible to save him.

311
00:20:38,773 --> 00:20:41,065
Of course.
That's my duty.

312
00:20:41,606 --> 00:20:43,940
I'll keep you informed on the progress

313
00:20:43,981 --> 00:20:45,690
Can I stay?

314
00:20:45,731 --> 00:20:49,565
(Surprised) Of course, you can stay
with him as long as you wish.

315
00:20:53,481 --> 00:20:56,190
I can't thank you enough.

316
00:20:56,231 --> 00:20:58,815
I'm at your disposal ma'am.

317
00:20:59,148 --> 00:21:01,606
Do you want me to stay with you?

318
00:21:01,648 --> 00:21:04,440
No, go on, love,
you've done enough.

319
00:21:05,648 --> 00:21:07,148
Should I bring you some food?

320
00:21:08,273 --> 00:21:10,815
No, don't bother
I'll get something later.

321
00:21:11,106 --> 00:21:12,481
I'll call you.

322
00:21:16,500 --> 00:21:18,958
(Whispers) Thanks...

323
00:21:31,958 --> 00:21:36,292
(doorbell)

324
00:21:55,148 --> 00:21:55,898
Who's there?

325
00:21:56,231 --> 00:21:57,356
It's Ray X.

326
00:21:57,398 --> 00:21:59,898
Ray X?
Nobody's called that.

327
00:22:00,190 --> 00:22:01,523
It's a nickname

328
00:22:01,856 --> 00:22:03,565
I used to do lots of ecstasy.

329
00:22:04,231 --> 00:22:05,065
What do you want?

330
00:22:05,606 --> 00:22:08,481
I want to write a script with you
and direct it myself.

331
00:22:08,731 --> 00:22:09,815
You're a director?

332
00:22:10,398 --> 00:22:13,231
I made a very good documentary
14 years ago.

333
00:22:13,273 --> 00:22:15,356
This would be my first fiction.

334
00:22:16,148 --> 00:22:18,940
Call my agent Judit Garcìa,
and talk to her

335
00:22:18,981 --> 00:22:22,023
She can make an appointment for you

336
00:22:22,273 --> 00:22:23,773
I'm going for a shower.

337
00:22:23,815 --> 00:22:25,898
You got me out of the bathroom.

338
00:22:32,023 --> 00:22:34,106
You gonna stay there all day?

339
00:22:34,148 --> 00:22:36,315
You didn't give me
Judit Garcìa's number

340
00:22:36,356 --> 00:22:39,648
Look it up.
She's a well-known production manager.

341
00:22:39,689 --> 00:22:40,981
I'm going.

342
00:22:41,731 --> 00:22:43,189
(off) Yes, go on.

343
00:22:54,583 --> 00:23:00,042
(mobile phone)

344
00:23:00,950 --> 00:23:01,792
Yes?

345
00:23:01,917 --> 00:23:03,333
Hi, Harry. It is I.

346
00:23:03,542 --> 00:23:04,625
Hi, Judit.

347
00:23:04,731 --> 00:23:07,856
A young director rang me.
Ray X.

348
00:23:07,898 --> 00:23:10,773
He wants to write a script with you.

349
00:23:11,106 --> 00:23:13,398
- You know about it? Yes
- He wants to see you this afternoon.

350
00:23:13,439 --> 00:23:14,898
Or tomorrow.

351
00:23:15,356 --> 00:23:18,148
I asked for an advance,
and he agreed.

352
00:23:18,398 --> 00:23:20,898
but I can't go with you,
I'm busy with the Americans.

353
00:23:21,606 --> 00:23:24,939
OK, I'll see him
and tell you about it.

354
00:23:24,981 --> 00:23:27,939
I hope you like him,
he seems to be well-heeled.

355
00:23:28,231 --> 00:23:29,439
Have you seen him?

356
00:23:29,481 --> 00:23:33,398
No from his voice,
and from the check he's going to sign.

357
00:23:33,439 --> 00:23:35,856
I'll send Diego so you're not alone.

358
00:23:35,898 --> 00:23:37,398
Ciao

359
00:23:42,773 --> 00:23:44,981
Alicante or Barcelone?

360
00:23:44,625 --> 00:23:45,792
Barcelona.

361
00:23:45,917 --> 00:23:50,667
The director really wants Barcelona.
I think Alicante it's a better option.

362
00:23:57,792 --> 00:24:02,125
(Doorbell)

363
00:24:03,167 --> 00:24:04,542
Hello.

364
00:24:04,606 --> 00:24:07,939
- I'm here to see Harry.
- Yes, he's in his office.

365
00:24:23,898 --> 00:24:25,314
Hi, I'm Ray X.

366
00:24:25,939 --> 00:24:27,148
How are you?

367
00:24:28,523 --> 00:24:29,814
Have a seat.

368
00:24:42,106 --> 00:24:43,023
I'm listening

369
00:24:43,939 --> 00:24:45,814
I really like your work.

370
00:24:45,856 --> 00:24:47,648
I've seen all of it.

371
00:24:48,731 --> 00:24:50,148
Thank you very much.

372
00:24:50,731 --> 00:24:52,731
Let's get to the point.

373
00:24:53,273 --> 00:24:55,354
What kind of story
do you want to write?

374
00:24:55,454 --> 00:24:57,958
(doorbell)

375
00:25:00,939 --> 00:25:03,731
I'd like to write a story about

376
00:25:04,231 --> 00:25:07,773
a son's revenge on his
father's memory.

377
00:25:07,814 --> 00:25:09,898
Why does the son want revenge?

378
00:25:12,356 --> 00:25:14,356
The father destroyed him
and ruined his life.

379
00:25:15,148 --> 00:25:16,064
How?

380
00:25:17,731 --> 00:25:20,398
The father is a violent man,
a homophobe.

381
00:25:20,439 --> 00:25:23,231
unscrupulous and very powerful.

382
00:25:23,273 --> 00:25:26,773
But the son is a sensitive boy,

383
00:25:26,814 --> 00:25:28,439
but he's got lots of complexes
and he's weak.

384
00:25:29,606 --> 00:25:31,939
He always tries to please his father.

385
00:25:32,148 --> 00:25:35,481
He's a homosexual but
he got married twice, like his father.

386
00:25:35,856 --> 00:25:37,773
And he separated,
like he did.

387
00:25:38,398 --> 00:25:42,481
He's got a son, who hates him
as much as he hated his father.

388
00:25:42,898 --> 00:25:44,648
When the father dies.

389
00:25:45,023 --> 00:25:47,439
the son can finally rebuild his life.

390
00:25:47,856 --> 00:25:50,689
That's his salvation, his revenge.

391
00:25:50,731 --> 00:25:52,481
and the story I want to tell.

392
00:25:53,106 --> 00:25:55,731
I fear I'm not the writer
you're looking for.

393
00:25:56,189 --> 00:25:57,356
You are!

394
00:25:57,856 --> 00:26:00,023
More than you know.

395
00:26:00,773 --> 00:26:01,981
I'll pay whatever you ask.

396
00:26:02,648 --> 00:26:03,814
It's too personal.

397
00:26:04,856 --> 00:26:06,356
Make it your own.

398
00:26:06,856 --> 00:26:09,606
Thank's, but no.
Now, if you don't mind... Diego!

399
00:26:15,106 --> 00:26:16,522
I'll leave you my number.

400
00:26:21,897 --> 00:26:23,647
If you change your mind.

401
00:26:23,939 --> 00:26:26,022
- Come along!
- Leave me alone!

402
00:26:28,231 --> 00:26:30,189
I'm sure we'll see each other again.

403
00:26:30,231 --> 00:26:32,022
In my case,
that would be a miracle.

404
00:26:32,064 --> 00:26:34,189
- Please, come with me
- I'm coming!

405
00:26:35,750 --> 00:26:37,792
Good bye.

406
00:26:40,833 --> 00:26:44,625
(leaves and closes the door)

407
00:26:47,064 --> 00:26:48,356
Son of a bitch!

408
00:26:52,064 --> 00:26:55,064
- He was talking about himself, right?
- I guess.

409
00:26:55,106 --> 00:26:57,189
Look in the top drawer.

410
00:26:57,772 --> 00:27:00,564
Look through the photos
of the '94 shoot.

411
00:27:00,606 --> 00:27:02,064
He may be in one of them.

412
00:27:25,231 --> 00:27:26,356
Keep looking.

413
00:27:44,231 --> 00:27:45,106
Here he is.

414
00:27:45,481 --> 00:27:46,897
Describe the photo.

415
00:27:47,606 --> 00:27:49,606
He's with you on the shoot.

416
00:27:49,647 --> 00:27:53,522
He's got long, straight hair
and he's holding a camera.

417
00:27:53,564 --> 00:27:54,897
I knew it.

418
00:27:54,939 --> 00:27:56,272
Who is he?

419
00:27:57,106 --> 00:27:59,106
Ernesto Martel's son.

420
00:27:59,147 --> 00:28:01,439
What can he want now?

421
00:28:03,439 --> 00:28:05,939
Put the photos away and
close the drawer.

422
00:28:29,667 --> 00:28:33,167
(phone)

423
00:28:33,939 --> 00:28:35,564
(Off Ex wife)
Ernesto, it's me.

424
00:28:36,939 --> 00:28:39,439
We have to talk about our son.

425
00:28:39,856 --> 00:28:40,814
Not now, Rosanna

426
00:28:40,856 --> 00:28:43,106
(Off) I caught him trying on my dresses.

427
00:28:43,147 --> 00:28:46,647
It's your fault. You made him
effeminate to humiliate me.

428
00:28:46,689 --> 00:28:49,439
(Off) I'm sending him to you.
After all, you're his father.

429
00:28:49,481 --> 00:28:53,772
If I haven't been a good father
for 19 years, I doubt I'll learn now.

430
00:28:54,106 --> 00:28:55,606
I have to go.

431
00:28:56,647 --> 00:29:00,147
And tell him if he wants to talk to me
he can call me himself.

432
00:29:01,731 --> 00:29:04,939
- Don't be so hard on them.
- Theyr'e blackmailers!

433
00:29:04,981 --> 00:29:07,106
- Help me with my necklace
- Of course.

434
00:29:08,022 --> 00:29:10,106
Why no invite your son here
for a few days?

435
00:29:10,147 --> 00:29:12,314
That's what his mother just said.

436
00:29:13,356 --> 00:29:16,814
(whispers) But it's best not
to involve you with them.

437
00:29:16,856 --> 00:29:18,272
He'd keep me company.

438
00:29:19,606 --> 00:29:22,856
- Does he like the cinema or theatre?
- Very much I think.

439
00:29:24,647 --> 00:29:26,814
His mother says
he's a bit of a fairy.

440
00:29:27,522 --> 00:29:30,897
If I invite him
I'd like you to tell me if it's true.

441
00:29:31,147 --> 00:29:32,731
and if it can be fixed.

442
00:29:33,564 --> 00:29:36,064
- How will I know?
- You don't have to screw him.

443
00:29:36,106 --> 00:29:37,314
Oh thanks alot.

444
00:29:37,564 --> 00:29:39,522
But you pretty girls
know those things.

445
00:29:39,564 --> 00:29:41,772
Call him, but I won't do that.

446
00:29:44,885 --> 00:29:46,104
(Off) This is shameful, Ernesto!

447
00:29:46,104 --> 00:29:48,355
What I don't like is
that you're living with a man.

448
00:29:48,397 --> 00:29:49,730
What'll your children think?

449
00:29:49,772 --> 00:29:51,730
That their father is homosexual.

450
00:29:52,189 --> 00:29:54,980
He's got good taste
and that hes lucky.

451
00:29:55,939 --> 00:29:58,439
If they love me, they'll accept it.

452
00:29:58,480 --> 00:30:00,980
(Off) You should've told me
before we got married.

453
00:30:01,022 --> 00:30:05,064
If you'd stopped thinking about
my father's fortune you'd have realized.

454
00:30:05,105 --> 00:30:05,980
(Off) What do you mean?

455
00:30:06,022 --> 00:30:07,980
I'm hangin up. Pain in the ass!

456
00:30:08,022 --> 00:30:09,480
I've got another call.

457
00:30:12,397 --> 00:30:15,939
- I hope it's not your other ex-wife?
- I hope not.

458
00:30:16,647 --> 00:30:18,147
Never get married, Mario.

459
00:30:18,189 --> 00:30:20,480
I'm not planning to right now.

460
00:30:20,917 --> 00:30:21,958
(Off) Hello?

461
00:30:22,314 --> 00:30:23,355
It's Judit Garcìa.

462
00:30:23,772 --> 00:30:25,647
Hi, did you get the money?

463
00:30:26,647 --> 00:30:28,022
I don't want it.

464
00:30:28,605 --> 00:30:30,855
I'm sending it back.
Ernesto.

465
00:30:31,480 --> 00:30:34,230
Won't you call me Ray?
That's my artistic name.

466
00:30:34,772 --> 00:30:36,230
Artistic?

467
00:30:37,147 --> 00:30:38,230
What are you trying to do?

468
00:30:38,272 --> 00:30:39,897
Erase my father's name.

469
00:30:40,647 --> 00:30:42,355
What's that got to do with Harry?

470
00:30:42,772 --> 00:30:44,897
I've wanted to see him for ages.

471
00:30:44,939 --> 00:30:48,439
And it's true I want to make a film
and have him write the script.

472
00:30:48,480 --> 00:30:50,439
I've got the male lead.

473
00:30:52,814 --> 00:30:53,939
You're not a director.

474
00:30:54,272 --> 00:30:57,272
If you saw my documentary
you'd change your mind.

475
00:30:59,605 --> 00:31:00,939
Ernesto, forget about us.

476
00:31:00,980 --> 00:31:04,022
Don't be afraid of me.
I'm not my father.

477
00:31:04,522 --> 00:31:06,355
Stay away from Harry.

478
00:31:06,397 --> 00:31:09,480
Or else I'll report you for harassment!

479
00:31:12,439 --> 00:31:15,355
I really don't want to
scout for locations.

480
00:31:15,730 --> 00:31:19,439
But the Americans are paying
me a fortune and we need it.

481
00:31:19,980 --> 00:31:22,897
Go on,
don't worry about me.

482
00:31:22,939 --> 00:31:24,897
Give me Tonino Guerra's book.

483
00:31:25,772 --> 00:31:27,689
I'm worried about Harry too.

484
00:31:28,022 --> 00:31:29,689
Look after him while I'm away

485
00:31:29,730 --> 00:31:33,147
I'm busy,
I can't spend all day with him.

486
00:31:33,189 --> 00:31:34,730
It's only 2 weeks.

487
00:31:34,772 --> 00:31:37,314
Harry's fine on his own.

488
00:31:37,772 --> 00:31:40,189
It's because of Ernesto Junior.

489
00:31:40,397 --> 00:31:43,064
If he shows up again or calls

490
00:31:43,105 --> 00:31:44,647
let me know right away.

491
00:31:44,689 --> 00:31:46,397
Why are you so worried?

492
00:31:46,439 --> 00:31:48,605
He's crazy.
I don't trust him.

493
00:31:48,647 --> 00:31:49,814
Why not?

494
00:31:50,439 --> 00:31:52,939
- It's a long story.
- Summarize.

495
00:31:53,522 --> 00:31:55,772
This isn't the time.

496
00:31:57,647 --> 00:31:58,855
For you, it never is!

497
00:32:00,105 --> 00:32:03,564
If you really mind looking after Harry,
i'm staying in Madrid.

498
00:32:03,605 --> 00:32:04,939
Or hire someone else.

499
00:32:05,772 --> 00:32:09,480
I don't mind keeping him company,
but I'm sick of all the secrets.

500
00:32:14,105 --> 00:32:15,564
When's your mother back?

501
00:32:15,855 --> 00:32:18,689
I'm not sure,
in ten days, I think.

502
00:32:23,605 --> 00:32:24,814
What are you looking at?

503
00:32:25,105 --> 00:32:26,814
A poster that says
"Give blood".

504
00:32:26,855 --> 00:32:28,605
- You want to give yours?
- No, no.

505
00:32:29,772 --> 00:32:32,439
I just like the sound of it.

506
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:34,855
It would be a great film title.

507
00:32:35,522 --> 00:32:36,772
It sounds good

508
00:32:36,814 --> 00:32:38,772
Like a vampire film.

509
00:32:38,814 --> 00:32:40,230
That's true.

510
00:32:40,439 --> 00:32:43,189
Imagine that behind the ad
there's a group of vampires

511
00:32:43,230 --> 00:32:47,522
who work in various donor clinics
they keep the donated blood

512
00:32:47,564 --> 00:32:49,355
and use it themselves.

513
00:32:49,397 --> 00:32:52,689
Your mother would like that story.
We'll write it.

514
00:32:53,708 --> 00:32:55,625
"Dona Sangre"("Give Blood")

515
00:32:55,772 --> 00:32:57,939
The vampires live like the Chinese,

516
00:32:57,980 --> 00:33:01,605
as part of Spanish society
but without attracting attention.

517
00:33:01,647 --> 00:33:04,397
and like the Chinese they
also control several industries.

518
00:33:04,439 --> 00:33:06,522
Like sunglasses, for example.

519
00:33:06,564 --> 00:33:10,438
And late night bars, discos,
after hours clubs.

520
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:14,730
They don't need drugs to stay awake
so they're the best night workers.

521
00:33:14,772 --> 00:33:16,522
And the sun cream business.

522
00:33:16,563 --> 00:33:20,522
They're sensitive to climate change
and to holes in the ozone.

523
00:33:20,563 --> 00:33:23,480
Their sun creams
are the best on the market.

524
00:33:23,522 --> 00:33:24,480
That's good.

525
00:33:24,772 --> 00:33:27,522
It must be a thick cream
like armor,

526
00:33:27,563 --> 00:33:29,147
