01:35:40,891 --> 01:35:42,016
I don't have her number.

1307
01:35:42,766 --> 01:35:45,308
Find "Elevator to the Gallows",
by Louis Malle.

1308
01:35:47,058 --> 01:35:48,308
Fritz Lang...

1309
01:35:48,641 --> 01:35:50,808
Jules Dassin, Nicholas Ray...

1310
01:35:50,849 --> 01:35:52,391
Look up above.

1311
01:35:55,141 --> 01:35:58,516
Fanny and Alexander, Fellini 81/2,
Magnificent Obsession...

1312
01:35:59,058 --> 01:36:01,433
Elevator to the Gallows!
Here it is.

1313
01:36:01,766 --> 01:36:03,057
I've never seen it.

1314
01:36:03,266 --> 01:36:04,807
I hope you like it.

1315
01:36:09,516 --> 01:36:11,016
(TV) How can I throw it out?

1316
01:36:11,891 --> 01:36:13,807
The police have to find it...

1317
01:36:14,141 --> 01:36:16,516
Leave it!
It's "Girls and Suitcases".

1318
01:36:17,266 --> 01:36:18,682
I don't understand.

1319
01:36:20,057 --> 01:36:21,307
It's simple babe.

1320
01:36:22,266 --> 01:36:26,057
If the cops find 30 pounds
of uncut cocaine in my house

1321
01:36:26,391 --> 01:36:27,641
they could arrest me.

1322
01:36:29,766 --> 01:36:34,016
But I don't understand how
that suitcase appeared in your house.

1323
01:36:36,182 --> 01:36:37,641
Doesn't it sound odd?

1324
01:36:41,891 --> 01:36:43,557
As I was saying,

1325
01:36:45,391 --> 01:36:47,516
after I split up with my husband

1326
01:36:48,391 --> 01:36:49,766
I went out on the street
and there was a guy eyeing me,

1327
01:36:50,016 --> 01:36:53,391
good-looking.
his ass... his feet...

1328
01:36:54,891 --> 01:36:56,891
I brought him home
and screwed him several times.

1329
01:36:57,141 --> 01:36:59,141
They're completely off key.

1330
01:36:59,391 --> 01:37:00,432
In bed?

1331
01:37:01,557 --> 01:37:02,641
A virtuoso.

1332
01:37:03,057 --> 01:37:05,182
Look, my hairs are standing on end.

1333
01:37:05,224 --> 01:37:08,141
How could I have chosen those takes?
They're both terrible!

1334
01:37:12,141 --> 01:37:13,641
What do you want to do today?

1335
01:37:14,891 --> 01:37:15,891
I have to go home.

1336
01:37:16,682 --> 01:37:21,057
Mom left a message that she's coming back today,
to celebrate your birthday.

1337
01:37:22,557 --> 01:37:23,766
It's my birthday?

1338
01:37:24,891 --> 01:37:26,141
That's what she says.

1339
01:37:26,891 --> 01:37:27,891
If Judit says so...

1340
01:37:29,141 --> 01:37:30,141
Happy Birthday!

1341
01:37:30,766 --> 01:37:32,932
I'll have to take you out to dinner.

1342
01:37:38,807 --> 01:37:40,516
Anyone at home?

1343
01:37:44,516 --> 01:37:45,766
Love,

1344
01:37:46,516 --> 01:37:48,057
I was dying to see you.

1345
01:37:51,891 --> 01:37:52,891
What's up?

1346
01:37:53,432 --> 01:37:54,891
Do they show a lot?

1347
01:37:56,432 --> 01:37:59,266
Today I didn't even have time
to wipe my ass.

1348
01:38:00,016 --> 01:38:01,516
Don't look at me like that.

1349
01:38:01,557 --> 01:38:03,307
I thought you'd be used to it.

1350
01:38:03,641 --> 01:38:04,682
Yes, I'm sorry.

1351
01:38:06,016 --> 01:38:08,182
You're so handsome!

1352
01:38:09,141 --> 01:38:11,807
Are you all right?
I was worried about you.

1353
01:38:12,266 --> 01:38:13,307
I'm fine.

1354
01:38:13,766 --> 01:38:15,557
Mateo looked after me day and night.

1355
01:38:15,891 --> 01:38:16,766
Mateo?

1356
01:38:17,891 --> 01:38:19,516
Don't you call him Harry anymore?

1357
01:38:24,557 --> 01:38:26,432
We have to buy him
a birthday present.

1358
01:38:28,891 --> 01:38:31,391
What have you been doing
all this time?

1359
01:38:31,641 --> 01:38:32,557
Nothing...

1360
01:38:32,891 --> 01:38:35,307
Watching films and talking.

1361
01:38:36,182 --> 01:38:37,057
Talking?

1362
01:38:39,391 --> 01:38:40,141
(Dry) About what?

1363
01:38:41,141 --> 01:38:42,391
Mom, for God's sake!

1364
01:38:49,432 --> 01:38:51,141
And what was wrong with you?

1365
01:38:51,391 --> 01:38:53,557
I'm not sure if
I believe the gastoenteritis.

1366
01:38:53,891 --> 01:38:56,266
You used it as an excuse in a script.

1367
01:38:56,682 --> 01:38:59,932
I had an accident, but I'd rather
not talk about it now.

1368
01:39:01,057 --> 01:39:02,307
An accident?

1369
01:39:03,141 --> 01:39:04,682
What kind of accident?

1370
01:39:05,766 --> 01:39:09,182
- It's hard to explain.
- Try, I'm not so dumb!

1371
01:39:09,516 --> 01:39:11,891
We'll leave it for another day.
I'm fine now.

1372
01:39:14,141 --> 01:39:16,557
I'm going to buy some DVDs for Mateo.

1373
01:39:52,932 --> 01:39:56,390
I don't know what you've talked about
all these days,

1374
01:39:58,140 --> 01:40:01,640
but I do know what I haven't told you
in all these years.

1375
01:40:02,140 --> 01:40:04,140
I never asked you.

1376
01:40:04,182 --> 01:40:07,265
But you'll have asked yourself
a thousand times.

1377
01:40:08,057 --> 01:40:10,307
This is your birthday present, Mateo.

1378
01:40:12,140 --> 01:40:14,015
It's also for you, Diego.

1379
01:40:19,515 --> 01:40:23,557
After you two disappeared,
Ernesto Sr. only wanted revenge.

1380
01:40:23,890 --> 01:40:24,890
- Forget it, Judit.
- No.

1381
01:40:26,182 --> 01:40:28,640
- You've had a bad day today
- That's why.

1382
01:40:28,932 --> 01:40:31,390
I'd like to end it better.

1383
01:40:33,265 --> 01:40:36,390
Ernesto had a crazy plan
to get his revenge on you,

1384
01:40:37,390 --> 01:40:40,265
but to carry it out
he had to bribe us,

1385
01:40:40,557 --> 01:40:43,390
at least, me and Luis, the editor.

1386
01:40:45,015 --> 01:40:48,140
Even though it was crazy,
there was no problem.

1387
01:40:48,557 --> 01:40:51,015
We both sold out
without any objection.

1388
01:40:51,307 --> 01:40:52,390
Luis and I.

1389
01:40:54,307 --> 01:40:55,390
With me,

1390
01:40:55,890 --> 01:40:58,557
he was courteous enough
to provide me with an alibi.

1391
01:40:59,640 --> 01:41:03,182
He suggested I went to the U.S.
for six weeks, to the Mayo Clinic

1392
01:41:03,515 --> 01:41:06,807
so Diego could be cured
of his aspergilosis.

1393
01:41:07,140 --> 01:41:10,140
That way,
I wouldn't be present while he...

1394
01:41:10,765 --> 01:41:12,515
destroyed your film.

1395
01:41:13,932 --> 01:41:16,015
Because that was his plan:

1396
01:41:16,890 --> 01:41:18,932
To reduce the film to rubble.

1397
01:41:25,140 --> 01:41:26,890
I prefered to stay in Madrid

1398
01:41:27,182 --> 01:41:28,932
and have Diego cured here.

1399
01:41:29,640 --> 01:41:31,515
I wanted to witness everything.

1400
01:41:31,807 --> 01:41:33,390
If I was to betray you,

1401
01:41:33,640 --> 01:41:36,057
I wanted to suffer the price
I had to pay.

1402
01:41:40,057 --> 01:41:41,557
It was torture

1403
01:41:42,432 --> 01:41:45,640
seeing how Ernesto chose
all the worst takes

1404
01:41:45,682 --> 01:41:47,140
and how Luis edited them,

1405
01:41:47,182 --> 01:41:49,890
turning your film into a monster.

1406
01:41:52,015 --> 01:41:55,765
The only way to bear all that
was to suffer more.

1407
01:41:57,057 --> 01:42:00,765
I sold myself to Ernesto
out of pain and jealousy.

1408
01:42:01,557 --> 01:42:03,307
I couldn't bear or forgive

1409
01:42:03,349 --> 01:42:06,890
that you left with Lena
without saying a word.

1410
01:42:08,015 --> 01:42:11,640
With my treachery, I got my revenge
on you, on her and on myself.

1411
01:42:13,807 --> 01:42:15,890
The only innocent one was Diego.

1412
01:42:17,765 --> 01:42:19,140
Forgive me my love,

1413
01:42:19,932 --> 01:42:23,015
for how bitter I've been
all these years.

1414
01:42:24,432 --> 01:42:26,932
No one deserves to grow up with that.

1415
01:42:44,307 --> 01:42:46,515
Another gin and tonic, please.

1416
01:42:55,890 --> 01:42:57,390
Don't look at me like that.

1417
01:43:22,807 --> 01:43:25,515
Don't go on.
It isn't necessary.

1418
01:43:27,307 --> 01:43:30,182
Now that you're calling yourself
Mateo again, I've got no excuse.

1419
01:43:30,515 --> 01:43:32,140
You've told us everything.

1420
01:43:35,515 --> 01:43:36,557
No, not everything.

1421
01:43:45,640 --> 01:43:49,307
No one knew where you were.
We had no idea.

1422
01:43:50,390 --> 01:43:52,265
Ernesto organized all that,

1423
01:43:52,515 --> 01:43:55,515
the premiere, all that fuss,
so that you'd react.

1424
01:43:56,057 --> 01:44:00,015
His revenge was meaningless
if neither of you responded.

1425
01:44:01,515 --> 01:44:04,765
He asked me constantly
about your whereabouts

1426
01:44:05,057 --> 01:44:08,265
but I knew nothing either,
which was true.

1427
01:44:08,557 --> 01:44:12,265
That's why I didn't wan't to call you,
so as not to complicate your life.

1428
01:44:13,765 --> 01:44:17,140
Ernesto hired various detectives
to look for you.

1429
01:44:18,390 --> 01:44:20,307
But before they could find you.

1430
01:44:21,432 --> 01:44:22,765
You called me

1431
01:44:23,682 --> 01:44:25,765
two days after the premiere.

1432
01:44:28,515 --> 01:44:32,682
I was too ashamed to answer

1433
01:44:33,807 --> 01:44:36,640
and too dazed.
I still am.

1434
01:44:39,432 --> 01:44:42,265
When Ernesto asked me
about you again,

1435
01:44:43,932 --> 01:44:45,265
I don't know why,

1436
01:44:46,515 --> 01:44:48,765
I gave him the number in Famara.

1437
01:44:53,182 --> 01:44:56,307
He sent his son
to look for you on Lanzarote.

1438
01:45:04,765 --> 01:45:08,182
It was Ernesto Jr.
who found you after the accident

1439
01:45:08,765 --> 01:45:10,265
and called the hospital.

1440
01:45:10,557 --> 01:45:12,682
Did he have anything
to do with the accident?

1441
01:45:14,515 --> 01:45:16,390
But I keep thinking

1442
01:45:16,432 --> 01:45:19,015
that if I hadn't given
that number to his father

1443
01:45:19,265 --> 01:45:21,557
perhaps nothing would have happened.

1444
01:45:24,682 --> 01:45:26,057
Why do you think that?

1445
01:45:28,765 --> 01:45:29,682
I don't know.

1446
01:45:30,932 --> 01:45:32,557
A guilty conscience, I suppose.

1447
01:45:32,890 --> 01:45:34,015
Well, that's enough!

1448
01:45:34,307 --> 01:45:37,140
14 years with a guilty conscience
is enough.

1449
01:46:04,890 --> 01:46:06,515
Wait, I'll help you down.

1450
01:46:09,432 --> 01:46:10,515
Good night.

1451
01:46:18,057 --> 01:46:19,765
Call if you need anything.

1452
01:46:39,625 --> 01:46:43,750
(mobile phone)

1453
01:46:46,431 --> 01:46:47,265
(Off answering machine) Diego...

1454
01:46:47,306 --> 01:46:50,056
Is not available.
Leave a message.

1455
01:46:51,681 --> 01:46:52,681
Hey Diego, it's Mateo.

1456
01:46:55,890 --> 01:46:57,640
I'm sorry to call so early.

1457
01:46:58,556 --> 01:47:00,515
Tell your mother to call me
when she can.

1458
01:47:34,515 --> 01:47:35,890
Harry, why so early?

1459
01:47:36,140 --> 01:47:37,556
I couldn't sleep.

1460
01:47:38,265 --> 01:47:39,306
Coffee and toast?

1461
01:47:39,640 --> 01:47:40,890
Yes, but first would you

1462
01:47:41,140 --> 01:47:43,390
call this number for me?

1463
01:47:45,890 --> 01:47:47,265
Ray X?

1464
01:47:54,640 --> 01:47:55,640
Here.

1465
01:47:56,515 --> 01:47:57,931
I'll get your coffee.

1466
01:48:00,515 --> 01:48:01,431
(Off) Who is this?

1467
01:48:01,765 --> 01:48:03,181
Sorry to disturb you.

1468
01:48:03,640 --> 01:48:05,265
This is Mateo Blanco.

1469
01:48:20,890 --> 01:48:22,306
Look at this!

1470
01:48:23,306 --> 01:48:25,140
You have to start the day well.

1471
01:48:28,515 --> 01:48:29,765
How do you feel?

1472
01:48:30,265 --> 01:48:32,640
A little bit hung over
but OK.

1473
01:48:33,765 --> 01:48:36,640
I think the catharsis last night
did me good.

1474
01:48:37,390 --> 01:48:39,931
- Let me help you
- No, sit down.

1475
01:48:46,265 --> 01:48:48,765
Yesterday I had one more thing
to tell you.

1476
01:48:49,056 --> 01:48:51,556
Tell me later.
We'll have breakfast now.

1477
01:48:51,890 --> 01:48:55,015
If I don't tell you now,
I may never tell you.

1478
01:48:56,931 --> 01:48:58,765
At the end of the 80s

1479
01:48:59,306 --> 01:49:01,890
Mateo and I,
had a love affair.

1480
01:49:03,265 --> 01:49:04,890
I thought so,

1481
01:49:05,140 --> 01:49:06,931
even before the catharsis last night.

1482
01:49:08,640 --> 01:49:10,056
- You did?
- It's obvious!

1483
01:49:10,098 --> 01:49:12,431
The same curtains
in your bedroom and in his,

1484
01:49:12,473 --> 01:49:14,515
souvenirs of Mexico and the Caribbean
in both houses,

1485
01:49:14,765 --> 01:49:15,890
the crosses...

1486
01:49:18,140 --> 01:49:20,140
There's something else you don't know.

1487
01:49:23,140 --> 01:49:24,765
Mateo is your father.

1488
01:49:25,931 --> 01:49:27,265
My father?

1489
01:49:30,765 --> 01:49:32,140
And the fleeting lover?

1490
01:49:33,015 --> 01:49:34,890
My supposed biological father?

1491
01:49:35,765 --> 01:49:37,015
Did you make him up?

1492
01:49:38,390 --> 01:49:39,931
I can hide things,

1493
01:49:40,265 --> 01:49:42,515
but I'm incapable
of making things up.

1494
01:49:43,640 --> 01:49:45,640
The fleeting lover existed.

1495
01:49:46,015 --> 01:49:48,140
We had an affair.
He was gay

1496
01:49:48,640 --> 01:49:50,806
and the affair was very brief.

1497
01:49:54,056 --> 01:49:55,515
Does Mateo know?

1498
01:49:56,681 --> 01:49:58,015
Are you crazy?

1499
01:49:58,431 --> 01:50:01,264
At the time he asked me
and I denied it, of course.

1500
01:50:02,014 --> 01:50:03,889
I didn't want
to pressure him

1501
01:50:04,181 --> 01:50:06,056
I didn't want that
to change our relationship.

1502
01:50:06,389 --> 01:50:08,806
And I'd never asked him
if he wanted to be a father.

1503
01:50:10,389 --> 01:50:11,306
Fuck!

1504
01:50:11,348 --> 01:50:13,306
So Mateo is my father...

1505
01:50:15,806 --> 01:50:18,139
By the way,
he rang early this morning.

1506
01:50:19,306 --> 01:50:20,764
Mateo? What did he want?

1507
01:50:21,139 --> 01:50:22,264
For you to call him.

1508
01:50:22,556 --> 01:50:24,181
Why didn't you wake me?

1509
01:50:24,514 --> 01:50:27,639
Because after last night you
needed to rest

1510
01:50:27,889 --> 01:50:29,431
and he didn't say it was urgent.

1511
01:50:29,764 --> 01:50:31,306
Pass me the phone.

1512
01:50:38,889 --> 01:50:42,306
Diego told me you called.
Are you OK? Do you need anything?

1513
01:50:42,681 --> 01:50:44,056
No, I'm not OK.

1514
01:50:44,389 --> 01:50:46,431
And yes, I do need something.

1515
01:50:47,014 --> 01:50:49,264
The 40,000 meters of negative

1516
01:50:49,306 --> 01:50:51,389
we shot in my last film, to edit it.

1517
01:50:52,764 --> 01:50:53,889
I'm at Ernesto Jr.'s house.

1518
01:50:54,514 --> 01:50:58,139
and I've found out that
the material was destroyed in '94.

1519
01:50:59,389 --> 01:51:01,181
I imagined something like that

1520
01:51:01,806 --> 01:51:03,431
but I didn't think
they'd do it so soon.

1521
01:51:03,473 --> 01:51:04,931
Why are you in Ernesto's house?

1522
01:51:05,306 --> 01:51:06,931
I think I'll blackmail him.

1523
01:51:07,889 --> 01:51:10,056
We need money
and he's got lots to spare.

1524
01:51:10,098 --> 01:51:12,514
I don't want Diego
going back to that damn bar.

1525
01:51:12,806 --> 01:51:14,514
I want to pay him a salary.

1526
01:51:17,181 --> 01:51:18,556
Don't be crazy!

1527
01:51:19,014 --> 01:51:21,556
There's no one else
to accuse of Magdalena's death.

1528
01:51:25,639 --> 01:51:27,389
Wait, I've got something to tell you.

1529
01:51:27,431 --> 01:51:30,056
Last night you said enough.

1530
01:51:30,389 --> 01:51:31,639
Listen to me!

1531
01:51:32,681 --> 01:51:34,889
I was production manager
on the film.

1532
01:51:35,181 --> 01:51:38,056
the only person with access
to the lab and the material.

1533
01:51:39,639 --> 01:51:43,639
After giving Ernesto's order
to destroy it, I intercepted it

1534
01:51:44,264 --> 01:51:45,139
I've got it all at home.

1535
01:51:46,431 --> 01:51:47,764
You're lying.

1536
01:51:48,764 --> 01:51:51,931
I didn't tell you last night because
I didn't know you wanted to edit it.

1537
01:51:52,806 --> 01:51:54,181
I took it all,

1538
01:51:55,014 --> 01:51:58,764
the double takes, the interneg,
the sound tapes, everything!

1539
01:51:59,139 --> 01:52:00,764
You can have it all.

1540
01:52:01,264 --> 01:52:02,264
That changes everything.

1541
01:52:02,306 --> 01:52:04,056
Get out of there, Mateo

1542
01:52:04,431 --> 01:52:06,056
and leave Ernesto in peace.

1543
01:52:06,389 --> 01:52:07,764
He's got nothing to do with this.

1544
01:52:08,014 --> 01:52:10,639
He still has to tell me
why he was in Lanzarote.

1545
01:52:10,889 --> 01:52:13,181
Bye, Judit.
I'll call you later.

1546
01:52:21,556 --> 01:52:23,264
Ernesto and his camera.

1547
01:52:25,014 --> 01:52:26,514
You remind me of a Peeping Tom

1548
01:52:29,139 --> 01:52:30,514
Yes,
but I never wanted to kill you.

1549
01:52:31,264 --> 01:52:32,639
I'm not so sure.

1550
01:52:35,639 --> 01:52:37,556
This copy of "The making of"
will prove it.

1551
01:52:39,889 --> 01:52:42,014
Why do I want it?
I can't see it.

1552
01:52:42,264 --> 01:52:45,014
Someone you trust can see it
and tell you. Excuse me.

1553
01:52:47,014 --> 01:52:49,764
These are the final images of
the documentary on Mateo Blanco,

1554
01:52:50,264 --> 01:52:51,889
also known as Harry Caine.

1555
01:53:37,139 --> 01:53:39,639
How's the "documentary",
as Ernesto calls it?

1556
01:53:42,139 --> 01:53:43,264
Very interesting.

1557
01:53:45,139 --> 01:53:46,306
